        <strong>T4 and T3 hormone production</strong>
        <p>Iodine is a structural component of both thyroid hormones. T4 contains four iodine atoms; T3 contains three. No iodine means no thyroid hormones — it is that fundamental.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="info-card">
        <strong>Metabolic regulation</strong>
        <p>Thyroid hormones set the basal metabolic rate for every cell. Insufficient thyroid hormones slow metabolism systemically, causing weight gain, fatigue, and cold intolerance.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="info-card">
        <strong>Fetal brain development</strong>
