    <!-- INGREDIENT BOX -->
    <div class="ing-box">
      <h4>Iodine: What the Science Says</h4>
      <p>Iodine is the essential mineral for thyroid hormone synthesis, with global health organizations ranking iodine deficiency as the leading preventable cause of intellectual disability worldwide.</p>

      <div class="vs-strip">
        <div class="vs-item">
          <strong>Thyroid Hormone Synthesis</strong>
          <p>Iodine is a structural component of T3 and T4 thyroid hormones. Without iodine, thyroid hormone production ceases, leading to hypothyroidism and metabolic decline.<br /><em>Endocrine Reviews, 2009</em></p>
        </div>
        <div class="vs-item">
          <strong>Iodine + Selenium Synergy</strong>
          <p>Selenium activates deiodinase enzymes that convert T4 to active T3 and protects the thyroid from oxidative damage during iodine utilization.<br /><em>Thyroid, 2017</em></p>
        </div>
        <div class="vs-item">
          <strong>Declining US Intake</strong>
          <p>Median urinary iodine in US adults has declined over 50% since the 1970s due to non-iodized salt use, lower dairy intake, and processed food manufacturing changes.<br /><em>NHANES, 2020</em></p>
        </div>
        <div class="vs-item">
          <strong>Pregnancy and Fetal Brain</strong>
          <p>One-third of US pregnant women have iodine levels below the WHO sufficiency threshold. Iodine deficiency is the leading preventable cause of intellectual disability worldwide.<br /><em>Thyroid, 2020; WHO</em></p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

